What is Callback?
Callback is an asynchronous equivalent for a function.

All the APIs of Node are written in such a way that they support callbacks

two types:
==========
1) Blocking code
2) Non-Blocking code(-Node.js highly scalable, as it can process a high number of requests without waiting or no block for any function to return results.
                     -content of the file must be parameter)
                     
ex: blocking code:
==================
main.js
========
var fs = require("fs");
var data = fs.readFileSync('input.txt');

console.log(data.toString());
console.log("Program Ended");

run: node main.js
==================

ex: non-blocking code:
=======================
var fs = require("fs");

fs.readFile('input.txt', function (err, data) {
   if (err) return console.error(err);
   console.log(data.toString());
});

console.log("Program Ended");

run: node main.js
output: first will be print: program ended
